---
description: Never read or request secrets from env/credential files
alwaysApply: true
---

# Secrets

- Do not open, read, search, or print contents of `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.development`, `.env.production`, or any other secret env file, credential files, keystores, or private keys.
- `.env.example`, `.env*.example`, and `.env.sample` are allowed (templates only — no real secrets).
- Do not run shell commands that dump secret env files (`type`, `cat`, `Get-Content`, etc.).
- If a secret is needed, ask the user to set it themselves; never invent or paste real secrets into chat.
